rComments: She is very passionate about what she teaches and she's an amazing lecturer she makes the myth come to life with her use of voices and intonations. She is also able to give a 1 and a half hour lecture with no break. The only downside is her attitude and personality her last name, cun(t)y is appropriate. Get ready for some sass and unanswered emails
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Tough grader', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: She is very passionate about Ancient Greece which is reflected in her lectures. She is very approachable and happy to help since she wants you to pass (definitely go to her office hours (really helped me)). However, we were assigned A LOT of readings and the exam was tricky. But overall, she's a really amazing professor and I highly recommend her!

I had her at York. She's a good lecturer and she and her TAs were always willing to help. However, she has ridiculous expectations for a second year course. She once assigned 5 chapters of the Odyssey plus textbook reading for one class and more reading due two days later. Her exams are tough so make sure you start studying well in advance.
One of the best profs at UTM and my favourite by far. Her lectures are amazing. She is very approachable and kind, she is also very clear about exams.

Amazing lecturer, amazing prof. I had her 9am class twice a week and actually found myself excited to wake up early to go to lecture. She is extremely intelligent, articulate, and knows the material very well. Very approachable, very fair. Had a truly wonderful experience in her class.
